<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.01/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi><note n="14" xml:id="d477fn14">This undated telegram was received on November 8,
                                1930.</note></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1930-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1930-11-07T17:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>1. Department’s telegram Nov. 7, 5 p.m., received and deciphered. It is
                            my opinion that the Provisional Government fully controls the country
                            and is supported by the people. Do not see the necessity of postponing
                            recognition until after Nov. 15, since conditions appear to be fulfilled
                            here which justified recognition of present Argentine Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>